Node.js @NODEJS_VERSION@ for @TARGET_TRIPLE@

This prefix was built by develop_suit packages/nodejs.

The package uses the Node.js source tree's bundled runtime components by
default, including V8, OpenSSL, libuv, zlib, nghttp2, nghttp3, ngtcp2, brotli,
cares, simdjson, simdutf, sqlite, uvwasi, and npm/corepack content shipped by
the selected upstream release.

For non-x86_64 Linux targets, bundled OpenSSL is configured with
--openssl-no-asm to avoid selecting host x86_64 assembly during Node's
cross-compilation configure step.

Linux packages also carry the target LLVM C++ runtime libraries and
libatomic.so.1 under lib/. ELF RUNPATH entries are patched to resolve those
libraries relative to the installed prefix.

Linux builds inject a small generated compatibility header through the target
and host compiler wrappers. It provides _GNU_SOURCE, MFD_CLOEXEC=1,
MFD_ALLOW_SEALING=2, memfd_create, and getrandom fallbacks through syscalls so
bundled V8 and libuv can build against older Linux headers that do not expose
those declarations by default. For loongarch64, an extra generated header also
provides HWCAP_LOONGARCH_LSX=16 and HWCAP_LOONGARCH_LASX=32 for bundled
simdjson and simdutf.
